  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b006",
    "text": "Two simple methods of characterization of the energy and energy spread of the electron beam have",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      167.0,
      504.5,
      178.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b007",
    "text": "been developed at the ESRF. Both are based on the analysis of the x-ray spectrum from an",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      178.0,
      504.5,
      189.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b008",
    "text": "undulator.",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      189.0,
      149.3,
      200.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b009",
    "text": "The first allows the absolute energy of the electrons to be determined. It is based on the",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      211.0,
      504.5,
      222.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b010",
    "text": "dependence between the harmonics’ wavelengths and the electron beam energy. The x-ray beam is",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      222.0,
      504.5,
      233.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b011",
    "text": "monochromatized at 21 keV by a silicon crystal in backscattering geometry. By adjusting the",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      233.0,
      504.5,
      244.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b012",
    "text": "magnetic gap, one makes the undulator third harmonic coincide with the energy selected by the",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      244.0,
      504.7,
      255.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b013",
    "text": "crystal. The electron beam energy is deduced from the gap value and the knowledge of the",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      255.0,
      504.5,
      266.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b014",
    "text": "undulator period and photon wavelength. The main errors come from the uncertainties regarding",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      266.0,
      504.5,
      277.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b015",
    "text": "the undulator parameters (magnetic field and period). The effects of the uncertainties in the",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      277.0,
      504.5,
      288.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b016",
    "text": "magnetic field are minimized by working at low field (K=0.37). The accuracy currently obtained is",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      288.0,
      504.2,
      299.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b017",
    "text": "better than 10-3.",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      299.0,
      171.0,
      310.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b018",
    "text": "The energy spread measurement is performed by a second method which is based on the change in",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      321.0,
      504.5,
      332.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b019",
    "text": "the shape of the harmonics’ profile with energy spread. It is deduced from the measured ratio",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      332.0,
      504.5,
      343.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b020",
    "text": "between the height of the seventh harmonic peak at 29 keV and that of the secondary maximum.",
    "bbox": [
      108.5,
      343.0,
      504.5,
      354.0
    ],
    "font_size": 10.0,
    "font_name": "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
    "label": "BODY"
  },
  {
    "pdf_id": "565",
    "page_number": 1,
    "block_id": "565_p1_b021",
